Patch Set 3:

I would recommend that you expand the following to accept an nid:

lnetctl net add --net tcp --nid 10.0.0.1@tcp

This can be added to the YAML document and sent to the kernel.

In lnet_genl_parse_local_ni() you can extract what you need:

} else if (nla_strcmp(settings, "nid") == 0) {
   ....
}

Sadly you will need to pass in a struct lnet_nid since struct lnet_ioctl_config_ni only support old style NIDs.
